GUWAHATI, India (AP) — Sri Lanka won the toss on Tuesday and opted to bowl in the first ODI against India. This is a three-match series following on from the three-match T20 contest between the two teams. India won the T20 series 2-1.Skipper Rohit Sharma makes a comeback to the Indian team after recovering from a finger injury sustained last month. Star batsman and former captain Virat Kohli also returns to the side. Both players missed the preceding T20 series.Fast bowler Jasprit Bumrah is out as he recovers from a back injury. He had earlier been included in the ODI squad for this contest. Ishan Kishan has been surprisingly left out from the Indian eleven. The opening batsman scored a record 210 in the last ODI India played against Bangladesh. Shubman Gill will open the innings with Rohit Sharma. Left-handed opener Shikhar Dhawan has been dropped owing to poor form. Fast bowler Mohammed Shami also returns to the Indian ODI side after being away since July.ADVERTISEMENTSri Lanka left-arm medium pacer Dilshan Madushanka will make his debut.The pitch at the Barsapara Cricket Stadium in Guwahati should aid batsmen and could produce a high scoring game. Heavy dew is expected in the evening and will aid the chasing side. SportsNo. 1 Georgia bullies TCU 65-7 to win 2nd consecutive titleBennett, Bowers lead champion Bulldogs' demolition of TCUGeorgia becomes 12th back-to-back champ in AP Top 25 historyBills safety Hamlin back in Buffalo to continue recovery—-Teams: India: Rohit Sharma (capt), Shubman Gill, Virat Kohli, Shreyas Iyer, KL Rahul (wk), Hardik Pandya, Axar Patel, Mohammed Shami, Umran Malik, Mohammed Siraj, Yuzvendra Chahal. Sri Lanka: Pathum Nissanka, Kusal Mendis (wk), Avishka Fernando, Dhananjaya de Silva, Charith Asalanka, Dasun Shanaka (capt), Wanindu Hasaranga, Chamika Karunaratne, Dunith Wellalage, Kasun Rajitha, Dilshan Madushanka.